Document: VisualShaderNodeGlobalExpression
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodeglobalexpression.rst
Summary: A custom Godot Shader Language expression that can be placed on top of generated shaders to define functions, varyings, uniforms, and global constants.

Inherits: VisualShaderNode < VisualShaderNodeExpression < VisualShaderNodeBase

Custom Godot Shader Language expression, which is placed on top of the generated shader. You can place various function definitions inside to call later in VisualShaderNodeExpression's (which are injected in the main shader functions). You can also declare varyings, uniforms and global constants.